{{Infobox monarch | name =Abu al-Hasan 'Ali' | title =[[Shah]] | image = | caption = | reign =997 - 1009? | coronation = | full name = | predecessor =[[Mamun I]] | successor =[[Mamun II]] | spouse = | issue = | royal house = | dynasty =[[Ma'munid dynasty]] | father =[[Ma'mun I ibn Muhammad]] | mother = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date =1009? | death_place = | date of burial = | place of burial = |}} '''Abu al-Hasan 'Ali''' (died c. 1009) was ruler of Khwarazm from 997 until his death. The second member of the [[Ma'munids|Ma'munid dynasty]], he was the son of [[Ma'mun I ibn Muhammad]].
In 997 Ali took over Khwarazm following his father's death. Little is known of his reign, but his emirate was dependent upon the [[Karakhanids]], rivals of the Ghaznavids.<ref>''The Early Ghaznavids'', C.E. Bosworth, '''The Cambridge History of Iran''', Vol.4, ed. R. N. Frye, (Cambridge University Press, 1999), 174.</ref> He died sometime around 1009 and was succeeded by his brother, [[Ma'mun II|Abu al-Abbas Ma'mun]].
