A '''leviton''' is a [[collective excitation]] of a single [[electron]] within a metal.<ref>{{Cite journal|url = |title = Minimal-excitation states for electron quantum optics using levitons|last = |first = |date = 31 October 2013|journal = Nature|accessdate = |doi = 10.1038/nature12713|pmid = |bibcode = 2013Natur.502..659D}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://phys.org/news/2013-10-experimental-pulse-generation-electrona-leviton.html |title=Researchers produce the first experimental pulse-generation of a single electron—a leviton |publisher=Phys.org |date= |accessdate=2013-11-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Francis |first=Matthew |url=https://arstechnica.com/science/2013/10/new-type-of-quantum-excitation-behaves-like-a-solitary-particle/ |title=New type of quantum excitation behaves like a solitary particle |doi=10.1038/nature12713 |publisher=Ars Technica |date=2013-10-23 |accessdate=2013-11-27|bibcode=2013Natur.502..659D }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://physicsworld.com/cws/article/news/2013/oct/24/new-leviton-quasiparticle-spotted-by-physicists |title=New 'leviton' quasiparticle spotted by physicists |publisher=physicsworld.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-27}}</ref>  It was first published in the journal Nature in 2013.  Levitons have been described in [[graphene]].<ref>{{Cite journal|url = |title = Graphene levitons and anti-levitons in magnetic fields|last = |first = |date = May 13, 2014|journal = Nanoscale|accessdate = |doi = 10.1039/C4NR00754A|pmid = |bibcode = 2014Nanos...6.7594F}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url = https://dspace.lboro.ac.uk/dspace-jspui/bitstream/2134/16547/1/RSCAdv2015_5_5442_DMF.pdf|title = Confinement effects of levitons in a graphene cosmology laboratory|last = |first = |date = 1 January 2015|journal = RSC Advances|accessdate = |doi = 10.1039/C4RA11227J |pmid = }}</ref>

