{{Infobox person |name = Nelly Arno |image = |caption = |birth_name = Nelli Aronowsky<ref name="birth"/> |birth_date = 15 July 1892 |birth_place =[[Karlsruhe]], [[Baden-Württemberg]], [[German Empire]] |death_date = September 1966 (aged 74) |death_place = [[Queens]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.<ref name="ssdi">Death of Nelly Aronowsky; ''Social Security Death Index, 1935-2014''. [[Social Security Administration]].</ref> |death_cause = |occupation = Actress |citizenship =United Kingdom |spouse = |children = }}
'''Nelly Aronowsky'''<ref name="gazette">{{London Gazette |issue=38436 |date=19 October 1948 | page=5533 |endpage= |supp=}}</ref> (15 July 1892 &ndash; September 1966), known professionally as '''Nelly Arno''', was a German-born British theatre, film and radio actress.<ref name=BFI>{{cite web|title=Nelly Arno|url=http://explore.bfi.org.uk/4ce2bafc07929|website=BFI|accessdate=22 July 2015}}</ref>
Aronowsky was born in [[Karlsruhe]] to Abraham Aronowsky and Fanny (''née'' Maysel). She had a younger brother, Alexander, born in 1896.<ref name="birth">Nelli Aronowsky, 15 Jul 1892; Alexander Aronowsky; 2 Jan 1896. ''Karlsruhe, Germany, Births, 1870-1904''</ref>
In 1920, she was living in [[Bernburg]] and already using the stage name Arno.<ref>''Deutsches Bühnen-Jahrbuch: Theatergeschichtliches Jahr- und Adressenbuch, 1920 (in German)''</ref> She was appearing on the English stage and radio productions following the Second World War.<ref>{{cite news|title=London Theatres: New Lindsey|url=http://www.britishnewspaperarchive.co.uk/viewer/bl/0001179/19490414/030/0007|accessdate=19 August 2017|work=The Stage|publisher=The Stage Media Company Limited|date=14 April 1949|location=London|page=7|language=en}}</ref> It's not apparent when she emigrated, but she became a British citizen in 1948.<ref name="gazette"/>
She died in [[Queens]], New York in September 1966.
